.
“神奇的2020，我们和股神一起见证历史。
"Mysterious 2020, we and the stock market together to witness history.
”　3月18日，美股因标普500指数盘中跌超7%，再次触发熔断机制，暂停交易15分钟，为美股史上第五次熔断，10天内第四次熔断。
On March 18, US stocks fell below 7 per cent in the S & P 500 index, triggering yet another meltdown, suspending trading for 15 minutes, the fifth in US equity history and the fourth in 10 days.
美股熔断时三大股指跌幅情况。
U. S. stock melts when the three main index decline.
此前，3月9日、3月12日、3月16日，美国股市已发生三次暴跌熔断，这三天道琼斯指数的跌幅分别达到7.8%、10.0%、12.9%，一次比一次跌得狠。
Earlier, on March 9, March 12 and March 16, the U.S. stock market had crashed three times, with the Dow dropping 7.8%, 10.0%, and 12.9%, one after the other.
现在，有人开始绞尽脑筋地想怎么减少熔断次数了。
Now, someone is struggling to figure out how to reduce the number of meltdowns.
美国芝加哥商品交易所(CME)17日对外表示，美国股市的熔断机制可能会调整，建议美国股市的熔断机制调整为只有7%和13%的下跌限制，要求ETF市场遵守相同的熔断规则，缩小ETF市场与其他市场价格差距，缓解交易日开始时市场交易量激增的状况。
The Chicago Mercantile Exchange (CME) on Tuesday said it was likely to change the US stock market's meltdown mechanism to a 7 per cent and 13 per cent cut-off limit, requiring ETF markets to adhere to the same rules of fusion, narrow the ETF market and other market prices and ease the trading surge at the start of trading.
历史上，美股熔断机制就曾修改过，2012年5月31日，纽交所修改指数熔断机制，一是以标普500指数取代道琼斯指数设置为熔断基准指数；二是将熔断阈值修改为7%、13%和20%三档。
Historically, the US-share meltdown mechanism has been modified, with the Nymex modifying the index fusion mechanism on May 31, 2012, by replacing the Dow Jones Industrial Average with the S & P 500 index as the Fusion Benchmark Index, and modifying the fusion threshold to 7%, 13%, and 20% of the benchmark.
沃伦·巴菲特 图片来源：视觉中国美股熔断规则是否修改还没结果，网友们已开启了段子接龙：　　3月8日，巴菲特：我活了89岁，只见过一次美股熔断。
Warren Buffett http: / / www.51education.net) www.51education.net) www.51education.net [hide] www.51test.net [/ color] www.51education.net) www.51test.net [/ url] www.51test.net [/ url] www.51test.net [/ color] Buffett: March 8, Buffett: I lived 89 years and saw only one meltdown.
3月9日，巴菲特：我活了89岁，只见过两次美股熔断。
March 9, Buffett: I lived to be 89 years old, only to see two U.S. stock meltdowns.
3月12日，巴菲特：我活了89岁，只见过三次美股熔断。
March 12, Buffett: I live 89 years, only to see three U.S. stock melts.
3月16日，巴菲特：我活了89岁，只见过四次美股熔断，我太年轻了…　　3月18日，我…　　“巴菲特说一辈子就看见五次熔断，我10天就实现了四次，看来我要比股神厉害。
March 16, Buffett: I live 89 years, only saw four U.S. stock melts, I am too young March 18, I... "Buffett said in a lifetime saw five meltdowns, I realized in 10 days, I seem to be better than the stock market.
”　　…　　15日(周日)，美联储曾突然放大招，“降息至零+量化宽松”，但市场并没买账，16日美股开盘就暴跌熔断。
The Federal Reserve abruptly scaled up its move Sunday by cutting interest rates to zero + quantitative easing, but the market did not buy it and U.S. stocks collapsed at the start of trading on Sunday.
截至3月16日，道琼斯指数、标普500指数、纳斯达克指数距离年内高点分别下跌了31.7%、29.7%与29.5%，均已进入技术性熊市。
By March 16, the Dow, the S & P 500, and the Nasdaq were down 31.7%, 29.7% and 29.5%, respectively, from their highs during the year.
当地时间3月17日，美联储祭出了通常金融危机时采用的“大杀器”——重启商业票据融资机制，此前，美联储动用这一工具分别是在2008年金融危机和大萧条时期。
On March 17, the Fed unveiled the usual "killer" of the financial crisis - relaunching the commercial-paper facility that the Fed used during the 2008 financial crisis and the Great Depression, respectively.
同日，美国政府也宣布要“直升机撒钱”，拟推出1万亿美元经济刺激计划，包括向美国民众发5000亿美元的支票，以缓解疫情对美国经济的影响。
On the same day, the U.S. government also announced plans for a $1 trillion economic stimulus plan, including a $500 billion check to the American public, to cushion the impact of the epidemic on the U.S. economy.
美股受到刺激17日上演绝地大反攻，暴力拉升。
U.S. stocks were stimulated on the 17th staged a stunning counterattack, violence increased.
全天道琼斯指数上涨5.2%，收复20000点和21000点关口；纳斯达克指数涨6.23%；标普500指数涨6%。
The Dow rose 5.2% throughout the day, recovering 20, 000 points and 21, 000 points; the Nasdaq was up 6.23%; and the S & P 500 was up 6%.
不过目前看，网友已提前成功预言了美股18日的走势：“美股坐了17天的过山车后，按剧情，不用猜，18日又暴跌！”　　美联储的“降息至零+量化宽松+金融危机大杀招”为何都不管用？　　中国社科院世界经济与政治研究所国际投资研究室主任、研究员张明表示，由于本轮金融动荡的根源不是债务危机、国际收支危机、货币危机与流动性危机，所以美联储通过货币政策救市的效果可能没那么好，除非美联储将量化宽松政策购买的资产扩展至美国股市的EFT甚至股票。
"After 17 days on the roller coaster, the Fed's" cut to zero + QE + currency crisis and liquidity crisis "may not work so well unless the Fed extends QE purchases to EFT and even equities in the US, said Zhang Ming, director of international investment research at the Institute of World Economics and Politics.
“应对疫情产生的风险冲击，更多需要依靠财政政策”，张明说，因为财政政策能够发挥结构性效果，但是发达国家财政政策要么空间不大、要么有些国家没想明白，所以财政政策协调一致要比货币政策难很多。
"We need to rely more on fiscal policy to cope with the risk shocks of the epidemic," Zhang said. "Because fiscal policy can have a structural effect, fiscal policy in developed countries is either too limited or not clear to some countries, so fiscal policy coordination is much more difficult than monetary policy."
市场普遍认为，只有更多的财政刺激措施出台且新冠病毒疫情停止恶化时，股市才会触底。
It is widely believed that the stock market will not bottom out until more fiscal stimulus is in place and the new crown virus outbreak stops worsening.
其中，疫情好转是核心要素。
Among them, the improvement of the epidemic is the core element.
瑞士信贷集团称，只有在新冠病毒的日感染率达到峰值以后，市场才会触底。
Credit Suisse Group says the market will reach bottom only after the peak in the daily rate of infection of the new crown virus.
目前，美国疫情持续“吃紧”，在西维吉尼亚州确诊首例病例后，全国50州均“沦陷”。
Currently, the United States epidemic continues to "tight," after the West Virginia diagnosis of the first case, the country's 50 states "fall.
据美国有线电视新闻网(CNN)报道，美国国家和地方卫生机构、政府以及美国疾病控制与预防中心的数据显示，美国已有7111例新冠肺炎病例，共有117例新冠肺炎死亡病例。
According to CNN, there have been 7,111 new cases of pneumonia in the United States and 117 deaths from new crown pneumonia in the United States, according to state and local health agencies, the government and the Centers for Disease Control and Prevention.
在16日的新闻发布会上，美国总统特朗普表示，最糟糕的情况是新冠肺炎疫情可能在7、8月或者更晚结束。
At a news conference on the 16th, US President Donald Trump said the worst scenario would be a possible end to the outbreak in July, August, or even later.
当被问及“美国经济是否正在走向衰退”时，特朗普的回答是“有可能”，这是他首次承认疫情暴发可能带来的可怕后果。
When asked whether the US economy is headed toward recession, Trump responded "Yes," the first time he acknowledged the dire consequences of an outbreak.
“每个国家，无一例外，都需要采取最大胆的行动。
"Every country, without exception, needs to take the bolder action.
”17日，世界卫生组织欧洲区域办事处吁欧洲国家采取大胆的措施。
On the 17th, the WHO Regional Office for Europe called on European countries to take bold measures.
日前，世卫总部已出现2例确诊病例。
There have been two confirmed cases at WHO headquarters.
“核心的金融市场期待的事情是看到切实的应对新冠肺炎疫情的举措，而不是简单的宽松放水。
"What the core financial markets are looking for is a real response to the outbreak of new crown pneumonia, not a simple water release."
”申万宏源研究副总经理、首席策略分析师王胜直言。
Wang Sheng, deputy general manager of Shenwen Hongyuan Research and chief strategy analyst, blurted out.
